  "doc_id": "46475",
  "text": "Cheah et al. [CITATION_1] provide empirical evidence that business model innovation provides competitive advantages to the retailers in the food industries. Their finding illustrates that the retailers acting in a high turbulence environment have a higher chance to get sustainable competitive advantages by re-innovation of their business model. Franceschelli et al. [CITATION_2] propose a framework to design a sustainable business model for a food startup in which, in addition to the economic profit, the social and environmental benefits are considered. Their study focused on a pizzeria startup in Italy.",
